<DOC><DOCNO> AP881022-0157 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-10-22-88 2150EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r w AM-Pepper 1stLd-Writethru a0660 10-22 0173</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Pepper, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0660,170</SECOND><HEAD>Rep. Pepper Hospitalized</HEAD><NOTE>Eds: UPDATES throughout with Pepper having growth removed.</NOTE><DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Rep. Claude Pepper, D-Fla., said Saturday hehad a ``small knot'' over a scar removed and that he expects to bereleased from Walter Reed Army Medical Center on Monday.   Pepper, at 88 the oldest member of Congress, said he had theoperation on Friday after the growth over a hernia scar wasdiscovered while he was ``undergoing routine tests at the end ofthe Congress.''   ``I will be out of the hospital on Monday and back on thecampaign trail next week,'' he said, adding that he had somefriends in to visit on Saturday night and enjoyed ``some wine withmy dinner.''   Jim Stueve, a spokesman for the hospital, said Pepper wasadmitted for ``medical observation'' and referred further queriesto the congressman's staff.   Charles Nichols, an aide on the Rules Committee that Pepperchairs, said the congressman would be out campaigning during theweek for Democratic presidential nominee Michael Dukakis.</TEXT></DOC>